→Ruby on Rails:</br>
or Rails, is a server-side web application framework written in Ruby under the MIT License.</br> Rails is a model–view–controller (MVC) framework, providing default structures for a </br>database, a web service, and web pages.</br> It encourages and facilitates the use of web standards such as JSON or XML for data transfer, and HTML, CSS and JavaScript for display </br>and user interfacing. </br>In addition to MVC, Rails emphasizes the use of other well-known software</br> engineering patterns and paradigms,</br> including convention over configuration (CoC), don't repeat yourself (DRY), and the active record pattern.
